## ♿ Accessibility Testing (Phase 4, Part 2)

### Test 1: Keyboard Navigation

**Dashboard:**
- [ ] Press Tab - focus moves to first widget
- [ ] Press Tab repeatedly - cycles through all widgets
- [ ] Press Enter on widget - opens widget (if interactive)
- [ ] Press Tab on WidgetManager - opens dialog
- [ ] Press Esc - closes dialog
- [ ] Focus visible on all elements (blue outline)

**Kanban Board View:**
- [ ] Press Tab - cycles through cards
- [ ] Press Enter on card - opens detail panel
- [ ] Press Esc in detail panel - closes panel
- [ ] Press Tab in detail panel - cycles through inputs
- [ ] Can't Tab outside detail panel (focus trap) ⚠️ **May need fix**

**Kanban List View:**
- [ ] Press Tab - cycles through table rows
- [ ] Press Space on checkbox - selects row
- [ ] Press Enter on row - opens detail panel
- [ ] Arrow Up/Down - navigate rows ⚠️ **Enhancement**

**Notes:**
- [ ] Press Tab - moves between sidebar and editor
- [ ] Press Cmd+K - opens search (quick switcher)
- [ ] Press Esc - closes search
- [ ] Can create/edit note with keyboard only

**Calendar:**
- [ ] Press Tab - cycles through days/events
- [ ] Arrow keys - navigate days ⚠️ **Enhancement**
- [ ] Press Enter on day - opens event dialog
- [ ] Press Esc - closes dialog

### Test 2: Screen Reader (macOS VoiceOver)

**Enable VoiceOver:**
- Press Cmd+F5
- Or System Preferences → Accessibility → VoiceOver

**Test:**
- [ ] Navigate to Dashboard
- [ ] VoiceOver announces "Dashboard" heading
- [ ] Tab to widget - VoiceOver announces widget title
- [ ] Tab to button - VoiceOver announces button label
- [ ] Open modal - VoiceOver announces modal title
- [ ] Form inputs - VoiceOver announces labels

**Windows (NVDA):**
- Download NVDA (free): https://www.nvaccess.org/
- Press Ctrl+Alt+N to start
- Same tests as VoiceOver

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ All interactive elements have labels
- ✅ All headings are announced
- ✅ Form inputs have associated labels
- ✅ Modals announce title when opened
- ✅ Status changes are announced (aria-live)

### Test 3: Color Contrast

**Tool:** WebAIM Contrast Checker
**URL:** https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/

**Test Light Mode:**
1. Screenshot any text on white background
2. Use color picker to get text color hex
3. Check contrast ratio - must be ≥ 4.5:1 for WCAG AA

**Test Dark Mode:**
1. Toggle dark mode (Settings → Theme → Dark)
2. Screenshot any text on dark background
3. Check contrast ratio - must be ≥ 4.5:1

**Priority Items to Check:**
- [ ] Body text (text-light-primary / text-dark-primary)
- [ ] Secondary text (text-light-secondary / text-dark-secondary)
- [ ] Priority badges (high=red, medium=yellow, low=blue)
- [ ] Status labels
- [ ] Button text
- [ ] Links

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ All text ≥ 4.5:1 contrast ratio
- ⚠️ If failing, note which colors need adjustment

