## 📱 Responsive Design Testing (Phase 4, Part 3)

### Test 1: Mobile Breakpoints

**Chrome DevTools Device Mode:**
1. Press F12 → Click device icon (or Ctrl+Shift+M)
2. Test these breakpoints:

**iPhone SE (320px width):**
- [ ] Dashboard: Widgets stack vertically (1 column)
- [ ] Kanban Board: Horizontal scroll (columns side-by-side)
- [ ] Kanban List: Some columns hidden, horizontal scroll
- [ ] Notes: Sidebar toggles to hamburger menu
- [ ] Calendar: Month view readable, events truncated
- [ ] Settings: All inputs fit width

**iPhone 12/13 (375px width):**
- [ ] Dashboard: Still 1 column
- [ ] Kanban: Same as 320px
- [ ] Notes: Better spacing
- [ ] Calendar: More room for events

**iPad (768px width):**
- [ ] Dashboard: 2 columns
- [ ] Kanban Board: Show 3-4 columns
- [ ] Kanban List: Show most columns
- [ ] Notes: Sidebar + editor side-by-side
- [ ] Calendar: Month view comfortable

**Desktop (1024px+ width):**
- [ ] Dashboard: 3 columns
- [ ] Kanban Board: Show all columns
- [ ] Kanban List: Show all columns
- [ ] Everything spacious and readable

### Test 2: Touch Targets

**Minimum:** 48x48px (Apple/Google guidelines)

**Test:**
1. Enable Device Mode (mobile)
2. Try tapping small buttons/icons
3. Check if all taps register easily

**Items to Check:**
- [ ] Dashboard widget controls (drag, remove)
- [ ] Kanban card actions (edit, delete)
- [ ] Notes sidebar items
- [ ] Calendar day cells
- [ ] Modal close buttons
- [ ] Dropdown selectors

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ All interactive elements ≥ 48x48px
- ✅ Adequate spacing between tap targets
- ⚠️ If too small, note which elements

### Test 3: Mobile Safari Issues

**Test on Real iPhone (if available):**
1. Open Safari on iPhone
2. Navigate to http://192.168.1.4:5174 (check dev server network URL)

**Common Issues to Check:**
- [ ] 100vh includes URL bar (may cut off content)
- [ ] Input focus doesn't zoom page (font-size ≥ 16px)
- [ ] Touch interactions feel responsive (no 300ms delay)
- [ ] Swipe gestures work (if implemented)
- [ ] Page doesn't bounce/scroll weirdly

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Page height adapts to viewport (including URL bar)
- ✅ Inputs don't trigger zoom
- ✅ Touch feels immediate
- ⚠️ Note any iOS-specific issues

